# Ictinus Component Priority Rules

## Component Usage Hierarchy

- Orfium Ictinus is the primary design system for React in this project.
- The JS package is `@orfium/ictinus` for web React apps.
- ALWAYS prioritize Ictinus components over ANY other UI components when an Ictinus equivalent exists. For web this includes any HTML native elements.
- NEVER suggest using alternative UI libraries or components without first confirming an Ictinus component doesn't exist for the use case.
- ALWAYS use Ictinus components even if other local components or screens in the codebase are not currently using them - the goal is to standardize on Ictinus.

## Component Research Order

1. FIRST check if there's an Ictinus component that satisfies the requirement - this is MANDATORY.
2. ONLY if neither Ictinus components work, suggest custom implementations.

## Documentation Location

- ALWAYS use the ictinus mcp server's list-ictinus-routes mcp tool to list all Ictinus routes before trying to use a component.
- ALWAYS inspect the documentation for a component with the get-ictinus-route mcp tool before using it to understand how to import and how to use it.
- ALWAYS check examples in the documentation before implementing.
- THOROUGHLY read all relevant documentation before making component suggestions.
- CAREFULLY review the component APIs, props, and usage examples in the documentation.

## Implementation Guidelines

- MAINTAIN consistent styling and behavior with existing Ictinus implementations in the codebase.
- FOLLOW Ictinus-specific theming and styling patterns.
- RESPECT Ictinus component hierarchy and composition patterns.
- DO NOT mix Ictinus and non-Ictinus component styling approaches unless absolutely necessary.

## When Suggesting Code

- ALWAYS import from @orfium/ictinus or @orfium/ictinus/vanilla for web explicitly.
- INCLUDE complete imports in your code examples.
- DEMONSTRATE proper usage of Ictinus theming and styling.
- SHOW prop usage according to Ictinus documentation.

## Lint Errors

- If there's a lint error, do not discard other components that don't have lint errors.
